item.title: M25 junctions blocked by Insulate Britain campaigners
item.description: Police make arrests as climate change protests take place at several locations around the motorway.

item.title: Covid: More than 300,000 suspected of breaking quarantine rules
item.description: It comes as the prime minister prepares to announce his winter Covid plan, including for booster jabs.

item.title: Trans man says confusion caused cervix-check delay
item.description: Jamie waited three months for an appointment after an abnormal result - it should be two weeks.

item.title: Four arrested after bodies of two men found in Bristol house
item.description: A murder investigation is launched after the bodies were discovered at a house in Bristol on Sunday.

item.title: Frank Fishwick: Murder arrest as army veteran dies after assault
item.description: Frank Fishwick died in hospital a day after being attacked outside his home, police say.

item.title: Emma Raducanu: Young players 'inspired' by her win
item.description: Young tennis players have been inspired by Emma Raducanu, the 18-year-old Grand Slam winner.

item.title: Rapist paramedic Andrew Wheeler faced investigation in 2010
item.description: Andrew Wheeler was jailed this year but first faced a police probe nearly a decade before the charge.

item.title: Rhamero West: Stab victim killed on day he started college
item.description: The family of Rhamero West, who was killed after a chase, says he died on the day he started college.

item.title: Reading Minster: Man arrested on suspicion of churchyard rape
item.description: A woman in her 20s was attacked near Reading Minster in the early hours.

item.title: Clacton stabbing: Two men, three boys and woman held in murder probe
item.description: The victim, a 21-year-old man, died in hospital after suffering a fatal wound, police say.

item.title: Brighton Marathon organisers apologise over course that was too long
item.description: Organisers of the event said they hoped it had not "marred the experience" for runners.

item.title: 'I want the most independence I can get'
item.description: Evie, from Loughborough in Leicestershire, dreams of being a nursery nurse like her mum.

item.title: Photographer's images 'like ghosts coming out the mist'
item.description: Guy Bellingham uses a 170-year-old technique to produce striking photos in remarkable detail.

item.title: What it's like to be given a zoo as a gift
item.description: Roughly 40% of the animals at Rutland Zoo come from other rescues.

item.title: Covid: The Chelmsford bench telling women's stories of the pandemic
item.description: Pippa Bloom, who had to shield due to Covid, says sharing her experience was "almost therapeutic".

item.title: 'We had tickets for Twin Towers tour on 9/11'
item.description: A couple reflect on how close they came to being caught up in the devastation of the 9/11 attacks.

item.title: 'Halo' saved my life - Hamilton relieved after crash
item.description: Lewis Hamilton says Formula 1's 'halo' safety device saved his life in his crash at the Italian Grand Prix.

item.title: Emma Raducanu: US Open champion's mental strength is truly special, says coach
item.description: Andrew Richardson, the coach who guided Emma Raducanu to her astonishing US Open triumph, says her mental strength is "truly special".

item.title: Harvey Elliott: Liverpool teenager suffers serious ankle injury at Leeds
item.description: A visibly upset Jurgen Klopp says Liverpool's Harvey Elliott was in "massive pain" after suffering a serious ankle injury at Leeds.

item.title: Manchester City 1-2 Tottenham: 'Literally two hands' in Spurs winner says Gareth Taylor
item.description: Manchester City manager Gareth Taylor says it was "literally two hands" from Spurs forward Rosella Ayane which helped them grab a controversial late winner.
